   <body>
      <context>This section explains the procedure to configure business logic in forms using the <uicontrol>FORM BUSINESS LOGIC</uicontrol> tab. The example fields and options selected in the procedure are for instructional purposes.<p>
            <uicontrol>Business Scenario Used</uicontrol>
         </p>
         <p>In an <uicontrol>Expense</uicontrol> form, if <uicontrol>Direct Expenses</uicontrol> is selected,  it has a <uicontrol>Purchase Order No</uicontrol> associated to it. Once the <uicontrol>Purchase Order No</uicontrol> is selected, you want to update the <uicontrol>Total PO Cost</uicontrol> for the associated <uicontrol>Purchase Order</uicontrol>.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Module</uicontrol> menu, click <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand the<uicontrol>Configuration Toolkit</uicontrol>folder, and then click<uicontrol>Form Builder</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>FORMS LIST</uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Import XML</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>IMPORT FORM</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To import the <uicontrol>Expenses</uicontrol> form, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Select <uicontrol>Form Import</uicontrol>.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>In the <uicontrol>Select Form</uicontrol> box, search for <uicontrol>Expenses</uicontrol> form, and select it from the drop-down list.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Click <uicontrol>Import</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>A form with the same <uicontrol>Form ID</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Form Header</uicontrol> of the <uicontrol>Expenses</uicontrol> form is created and displayed in the <uicontrol>FORMS LIST</uicontrol> page.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To modify and update the <uicontrol>Expenses</uicontrol> form, select the form, and click <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the controls pane, click <uicontrol>SIMPLE INPUT CONTROLS</uicontrol>, and then drag and drop <uicontrol>Numeric</uicontrol> control to the design area.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Double-click the <uicontrol>Numeric</uicontrol> control and enter <uicontrol>Total PO Cost</uicontrol> for the text box.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To make the <uicontrol>FORM BUSINESS LOGIC</uicontrol> tab available, in the toolbar, click <uicontrol>Switch to Advanced</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the <uicontrol>FORM BUSINESS LOGIC</uicontrol> tab.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the controls pane, from the <uicontrol>Select Event</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the <uicontrol>Form Load</uicontrol> event.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/FormLoad.jpg" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Expand the <uicontrol>DEFINITIONS</uicontrol> block and click the <uicontrol>Variables</uicontrol> block.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_BL_Form_Variable.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Create Variable</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>A pop-up message appears to provide the variable name.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_BL_Form_CreateVariable.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>New variable name</uicontrol> field, enter the variable name as <msgph>POValue</msgph>, and click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The newly created variable is available in the variable list with the <uicontrol>set</uicontrol> operator.<fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_BL_Form_Set_variable.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drag and connect the <uicontrol>set</uicontrol> operator to the <uicontrol>Form Load</uicontrol> event.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/set_opr_FormLoad.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Expand the <uicontrol>DATA OPERATIONS</uicontrol> block and click the <uicontrol>Read Data</uicontrol> block.</p>
            <p>The available options of the <uicontrol>Read Data</uicontrol> block are displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drag and connect the <uicontrol>SELECT</uicontrol> block to the <uicontrol>set</uicontrol> operator.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>SELECT</uicontrol> block, select the <uicontrol>Module</uicontrol> as <msgph>Project</msgph>, <uicontrol>Form</uicontrol> as <msgph>Purchase Order</msgph>, and <uicontrol>Field</uicontrol> as <msgph>Revised PO Value in {_LOC:LOC_CURRENCY_SYMBOL}:</msgph>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_Form_SELECT_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>WHERE</uicontrol> block, select the <uicontrol>Module</uicontrol> as <msgph>Project</msgph>, <uicontrol>Form</uicontrol> as <msgph>Purchase Order</msgph>, and <uicontrol>Field</uicontrol> as <msgph>PR Ref Number</msgph>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_Form_WHERE_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To equate the conditions of the <uicontrol>SELECT</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>WHERE</uicontrol> blocks, click the <uicontrol>GET</uicontrol> block under the <uicontrol>DATA OPERATIONS</uicontrol> block and drag and connect the <uicontrol>Get Value of</uicontrol> field to the <uicontrol>WHERE</uicontrol> block.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_Form_Get_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the value of the <uicontrol>Get Value of</uicontrol> field as <msgph>Purchase Order No:</msgph>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_Form_Get_Value_of_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Expand the <uicontrol>ACTIONS</uicontrol> block and click <uicontrol>Set</uicontrol> block.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drag and connect the <uicontrol>Set Value of</uicontrol> field to the <uicontrol>Form Load</uicontrol> event.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the value of the <uicontrol>Set Value of</uicontrol> field as <msgph>Total PO Cost</msgph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the <uicontrol>GET</uicontrol> block under the <uicontrol>DATA OPERATIONS</uicontrol> block, and drag and connect the <uicontrol>Get Property of</uicontrol> to the <uicontrol>Set Value of</uicontrol> field.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the value of the <uicontrol>Get Property of</uicontrol> field as <msgph>POValue</msgph> and in the next drop-down list, select the value as <msgph>PurchaseOrder. Revised PO Value in {_LOC:LOC_CURRENCY_SYMBOL}:</msgph>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title/>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Config_Form_Get_Property_of_block.jpg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Publish</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
